content.description: This route passes near the west end of the upper south face but near this corner the usable hold cease in the upward path and must be taken up to the right.  The needed clip is not so easy on this traverse.
content.location: From the south saddle of the Main Tower near the western side climb toward the square west corner and work up and right.

content.description: a steep start leads to cul de sac of bulges to choose from and once out the going gets easier.  On the left this pitch joins route to left.
content.location: The route begins at next lower ledge west from the west end of the south saddle of the Main Tower

content.description: On this sport route just bounce up through some roofs and rightward on bigger holds.
content.location: This route begins 2nd route right on the south saddle of the Main Tower

content.description: Moderate face above the corner start leads to some shallow groves and holds near a corner with no bite on top of them.  You'll feel you can just walk off to the left on the smallish ledge on the left.  Do it without any holds?
content.location: Start on the very SW corner of Main Tower next to a vertical gully.

content.description: This very long pitch makes use of the Main Tower's longest face by beginning near the lowest point on the SW corner.  After a steeper start than the rest of face the route moves to the easiest turf at each option.
content.location: Begin about 30 feet uphill [left] of the SW corner of Main Tower.
